	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Seven people have been killed following a crash on the R614 near Appelsbosch in KwaZulu-Natal, paramedic services have said. EMS spokesperson Robert Mckenzie said one other person had sustained critically injuries and was taken to hospital. "The cause of the crash, between a car and bakkie, is unknown at this stage," he said. Police were on the scene to investigate.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.